history.content:
<md>CS188 is a superfun class (especially when Prof. Dragan teaches it) with relatively light assignments and projects. However, it does have very difficult exams to balance this out (the curve will save you here, so don't worry.) If you have no idea if you like AI or ML, this is a good survey class that teaches you about all of the different aspects of these fields (reinforcement learning, neural networks, etc.)

EE16B is somewhat of a survey class for EE/EECS fields. It is a higher workload class with weekly PS, exams, and labs. Pretty time consuming if you don't know what you are doing. It is a class that you should get out of the way as soon as you can (if you need it to graduate). Would recommend you take EE16B as soon as possible since enrollment gives priority to freshmen and sophomores, and taking it later will be a pain.

Really depends on what classes you are taking along side them and how much time you have for other stuff.</md>

children.subject: I personally didn't like 188 and thought 16B was easier even though I was dreading it. I wish I had taken 16B a lot earlier in college because it would have given me more motivation for everything you learn in the upper divs and would have made me feel more excited about cs. I liked 189 a lot better than 188 and even Data 100 prepared me for it. I didn't like the first half of 16B but if you push through I think people who like cs will like the second half a lot better especially when you see all the big ideas and the cool ways you can apply what your learning.
